            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Perhaps I don't understand this issue, but maybe it should be closed. It seems like current flask versions allow error handlers for any kind of exception.  By this I mean the following program runs without an error, there are all sorts of combinations and permutations which it doesn't test.    \n\n```\n    import flask\n    app = flask.Flask(__name__)\n\n    @app.errorhandler(Exception)\n    def handle_500(x=None):\n            print \"Trapped a python Exception!\"\n            return \"app trapped\", 200\n\n    @app.route('/')\n    def slash_view() :\n            raise Exception(\"WTF?\")\n\n    c = app.test_client()\n    resp = c.get('/')\n    assert resp.data == \"app trapped\"\n    assert resp.status_code == 200\n```\n"
        },
