            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It's been a while, but I think the main idea here is to make HTTP exceptions fully fledged response objects. This is still valid.\n\nThe code for _handling_ errors has been refactored to not make that much of a difference between HTTP and other exceptions, see https://github.com/pallets/flask/pull/1291. But that's not the main point of this issue anyway.\n"
